8.0 Summoning
:SKRSLUT.
.br
:SWISS8.
The insurance sum payable for accommodation expenses is up to DKK 1,800
per person per day, to a maximum of DKK 27,000 per claim.
.br
Unlimited travel expenses, although at no more than economy class.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS8.
:FED.
8.1 Coverage
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The insurance covers reasonable expenses for travel, accommodation and
travel insurance for no more than two people who, by arrangement with
SOS International, are summoned to be with the insured in the event of
him/her suffering an acute and serious illness, serious injury or death.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Privatsikring's compensation obligation is subject to the following
conditions:
.br
- the hospital stay is expected to last at least three days from the date
of hospitalisation
.br
- the insured is not to be repatriated in connection with the illness or
injury within three days.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
8.2 Compensation
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The maximum compensation payable for accommodation expenses, including
meals, is DKK 1,800 per person per day, and no more than DKK 27,000 in
total per claim. Compensation for travel expenses cannot exceed the price
for an economy class airline ticket.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
8.3 Reporting claimsade
:SKRSLUT.
.br
In the event of illness/injury, SOS International must always be informed
without delay and will then determine whether and when relatives can be
summoned.
.br
On returning home, a claim report is to be submitted to Privatsikring
together with documentation for travel expenses, accommodation etc.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
