:FED.
9.0 Delayed flights and connections
:SKRSLUT.
.br
:SWISS8.
Insurance sum payable: DKK 6,000 per person.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
9.1 Coverage
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The insurance provides coverage in the following situations:
.of 5mm
*¤When the reserved flight is delayed for more than four hours.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤When the reserved flight is cancelled.
.of
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤When the insured, through no fault of his/her own, fails to board the
reserved flight on account of overbooking or through late arrival due
to a documented delay of a connecting flight, and no alternative
flight is available.
.of
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
9.2 Compensation
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The insurance covers necessary and reasonable expenses for meals and
accommodation - if appropriate - in the amount of up to DKK 6,000 per
journey per person. In addition, compensation is payable in the maximum
amount of DKK 500 per journey to cover reasonable and necessary
expenses for clothes and toiletries in connection with overnight stays.
.br
The expenses must have been paid where the delay took place, and will
be refunded on presentation of original receipts.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
9.3 Exceptions
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The insurance does not provide coverage for flights delayed in the
insured's country of residence. However, this exception does not apply
to Article 3 in Section 9.1.
.br
Nor does the insurance apply in the event that an alternative flight
is offered with a departure no more than four hours after the
originally planned departure time.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
9.4 Reporting claims
:SKRSLUT.
.br
On returning home, a claim report is to be submitted to
Privatsikring together with the airline ticket, information about
the flight number, point of departure and destination, the airline
report on the delay, and the original receipts.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
